// Tailspot.xcconfig — committed, public build configuration.
//
// The app no longer ships any API secret in its binary: OpenSky (the
// only credentialed source) was removed in the 2026-06-21 cutover, so
// there are no OAuth credentials to bake in. ADS-B now comes solely from
// the Tailspot backend (api.tailspot.app), which needs no per-app secret.
//
// The one remaining build-time secret is the PostHog analytics key, which
// is OPTIONAL — when absent the app simply disables analytics.
//
// POSTHOG_API_KEY: PostHog project API key for anonymous product analytics.
// When absent or empty, Analytics is a silent no-op (zero network).
// See ios/Tailspot/Tailspot/Analytics.swift for the full privacy posture.
//
// It lives in `Tailspot.secrets.xcconfig` (gitignored, never committed),
// included below via the optional-include directive `#include?` — if the
// file is missing there's no build error. The secrets file, when present,
// gets included AFTER this default, so its assignment overrides
// (last-wins is xcconfig precedence). It flows into Info.plist via the
// $(POSTHOG_API_KEY) substitution there.
//
// To set up the key locally: copy Tailspot.secrets.example.xcconfig to
// Tailspot.secrets.xcconfig and paste the value (clean build after — Xcode
// caches resolved Info.plist values per-build).
POSTHOG_API_KEY =

#include? "Tailspot.secrets.xcconfig"
